cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of Fisher information and natural gradient in artificial neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses optimization techniques, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on large and complex models suggests the possibility of cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
